							<h3 align="center"> Two days ‘National Workshop’ of convergence within FDDI, IIFT, IIP, NID & NIFT held </h3>

						<p align="justify"> The two days ‘National Workshop’ of convergence within five institutes namely, Footwear Design and Development Institute (FDDI), Indian Institute of Foreign Trade (IIFT), Indian Institute of Packaging (IIP), National Institute of Design (NID) and National Institute of Fashion Technology (NIFT) was held on 31st May and 1st June 2023 at New Delhi.  </p>
						<p align="justify"> On 1st June 2023, the Hon'ble Minister of Commerce and Industry, Consumer Affairs, Food and Public Distribution and Textiles (HCIM, CA, F&PD&T), Government of India (GoI), Mr. Piyush Goyal chaired the meeting and interacted with the Heads and Senior Faculty Members of these educational institutes. </p>
						<p align="justify"> On this occasion, Secretary, Department for   Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT), Mr. Rajesh Kumar Singh, Additional Secretary, DPIIT, Mr. Rajeev Singh Thakur and other senior oﬃcials from various departments and other institutes were also present. </p>
						<p align="justify"> The convergence of the five institutes under the Ministry of Textiles and Commerce and Industry was initiated in the month of November 2022. The collaboration between these five institutes has the ability to build a more dynamic and integrated national design and business education ecosystem that benefits students, industries, and society. </p>
																																																																																		
						<span class="news-details-img">
						<img class="img-responsive" src="img/new@fddi/national-workshop-img.JPG" alt="img">						
						</span>						
						
						<p align="justify"> The HCIM, CA, F&PD&T said that fashion trends, product design, innovative packaging, high quality of goods and services and high exports are going to determine India’s success story in the future. </p>
						<p align="justify"> He further said that India’s transformational journey since 2014 under the leadership of our Hon’ble Prime Minister, Mr. Narendra Modi is now recognized globally, and drew attention to Morgan Stanley research report which also recognizes how India has emerged as a key driver for Asian and global growth. </p>
						<p align="justify"> He highlighted the role played by the alumni of these institutions with respect to donation, faculty, mentorship, etc. He focused on better placements from these institutes.  </p>
						<p align="justify"> On this occasion, Mr. Arun Kumar Sinha, IAS, Managing Director (MD), FDDI, Mr. Pankaj Kumar Sinha, Secretary, FDDI, Senior Faculty Members from FDDI namely Mr. Sandeep Bhatia, Dr. Prachi Sharma, Ms. Shweta Saini, Mr. Sharad Srivastava, Mr. Amit Verma, Ms. Sarika Tandon and Mr. Himanshu Baluni and distinguished alumni namely Mr. Ankur Rastogi – VP Collection, Bata India, Mr. Chetan Sarasawat - Founder, ATI Impex, Mr. Aarush Mehta - Business Head, Chemico Processing, Ms. Anima - VM Head, Mango, Mr. Pulkit Nijhawan - CEO, Milano Mode, Mr. Sameer Sharma - Managing Director, Sainath Industries, Mr. Rahul Kumar - Founder, Welvart Trading, Mr. Dharmender Sir - Founder, Gopsun Leathers, Mr. Biplab - Founder, Brand Forever, Mr. Suman Nayak - National Sales, Nippon Audiotronix, Ms. Kiran – Sr. Consultant, FDDI, Mr Vijay Jha - MD Savi Leathers were present. </p>
						<p align="justify"> From FDDI, the presentation was given by Mr. Anoop Singh Rana, Head of School of Leather Goods & Accessories Design (LGAD). </p>
						<p align="justify"> Deliberations and work have been done to pave the path to achieve the following objectives: Convergence within Institutes, Student Promotional Schemes, Admission Process and Growth in student enrolment, Creating a Professional Network of Alumni and Industry-Academia Collaboration. </p>
																											
